OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FUntil that time, I had no idea what
OL,7,Fhospices really did. To me, I
OL,8,Fignorantly thought they were nice
OL,9,Fplaces where old people went to die.
OL,11,FI soon discovered that ignorance is
OL,12,Fwidely shared, as is the
OL,13,Funderstanding, or lack of, of how
OL,14,Fhospices are actually funded.
OL,16,FThe work of hospices is both precious
OL,17,Fand precarious. The vast majority of
OL,18,Fend-of-life care that they deliver is
OL,19,Fpaid for through donations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/28
