OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FMy mum died with dignity, at home,
OL,7,Fbecause someone somewhere held a
OL,8,Fcoffee morning, or donated some old
OL,9,Fclothes to their local charity shop,
OL,10,For ran a marathon.
OL,12,FThe government provides, on average,
OL,13,Fjust a third of hospice funding.
OL,14,FChildren's hospices receive even less.
OL,16,FIt costs around #1.6 billion a year to
OL,17,Frun the UK's 200 or so hospices. #1.1
OL,18,Fbillion of that is raised by the
OL,19,Fhospices themselves through
OL,20,Ffundraising.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/28
