OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FThat is hard enough in good times, but
OL,7,Fin both economic and health terms,
OL,8,Fthese are not good times. To put it
OL,9,Fbluntly, slowly but surely hospices
OL,10,Fare running out of money.
OL,12,FAn ageing population living longer
OL,13,Fwith terminal health conditions means
OL,14,Fhospices are treating more people than
OL,15,Fever, at a time when the cost of
OL,16,Fliving is limiting the amount of money
OL,17,Fcoming through the door in donations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/28
