OL,6,F"Mum was a force of nature," she said.
OL,8,F"She was the glue that held my life
OL,9,Ftogether. She was the witness to my
OL,10,Flife, the witness to the most mundane
OL,11,Fthings. She was our cheerleader.
OL,13,F"It just caught us completely out of
OL,14,Fthe blue. She'd been unwell, and the
OL,15,Fdoctors weren't sure what it was.
OL,17,F"A part of my brain was like, surely
OL,18,Fnot, surely this can't happen again so
OL,19,Fsoon to our family? It's not our turn
OL,20,Fagain, surely?"
