OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,F"When it got to that point where she
OL,7,Fcould no longer be at home...she
OL,8,Fdidn't want to be at hospital. She
OL,9,Fwanted to be in a hospice."
OL,11,FDespite becoming seriously ill only
OL,12,Ffour years apart, the contrast in care
OL,13,FTony and Kim received could not have
OL,14,Fbeen more different.
OL,16,FNatalie watched as the careful
OL,17,Frequests her mum had made for a
OL,18,Fdignified death failed to materialise.
OL,19,FShe says Kim's hospice stay was no
OL,20,Fdifferent to being in an over-run,
OL,21,Funder-resourced hospital.
