OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FThere are of course many other reasons
OL,7,Fwhy some people support assisted
OL,8,Fdying, but the consequences for an
OL,9,Falready struggling hospice sector is
OL,10,Fcurrently unclear.
OL,12,FFundraising, the goodwill and
OL,13,Fgenerosity of strangers, can only go
OL,14,Fso far in funding palliative care.
OL,15,FHospice are begging for sustainable
OL,16,Ffunding from the government to
OL,17,Fcomplement the enormous amount of
OL,18,Ffundraising they undertake to continue
OL,19,Ftheir incredible work.
